git init
git add .
git commit -m "first commit"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/balu1391/git-commands.git
git push -u origin main

git pull origin main 

error :- fatal: refusing to merge unrelated histories

try :- git pull origin main --allow-unrelated-histories

Difference between git reset and git revert
------------------------------------

git reset :- 1) it remove files from working directory / it get back files to untracked area
             
             2) git reset <commit-id>    -- moves the pointer back to the commit you specify  -- if u change 4 to 2 -- only 2 commits wii be there
             
             3) git reset --hard HEAD~1   --- it deletes the commits also
             
 git revert :- git revert creates another commit at the end of the chain to cancel the change.
  